title: For Sale:  INLAND M1 Carbine
postcontent:
Inland Manufacturing M1A1 Paratrooper 

The M1A1 carbines feature many of the same characteristics of the original Inland Carbines and are manufactured in the USA!

The M1A1 carbine is modeled after a late production 1944 M1A1 Paratrooper model with a folding "low wood" walnut stock, type two barrel band, and includes the same adjustable sights which were actually introduced in 1944.

The M1A1 includes a 15-round magazine and offers the same common features of the 1945 M1 model. Attention to detail has been carefully taken to produce a replica as close as possible to the original Inland production including cartouche marks and stampings in the wood specific features of the Inland Carbines.

In 1941, with the US being pulled into one of the greatest conflicts in world history, a division of General Motors was tasked to support the war effort.

The result was firearm history with Inland Manufacturing becoming one of the largest gun manufacturers in the US, producing nearly 3 million firearms in less than 5 years.

The most notable of Inland's firearm production was the .30 Caliber M1 carbine and the folding stock variant, the M1A1 Paratrooper model.

title: For Sale/Trade:  2003 Hyundai Tiburon 2.7l V6 GT A.K.A War Machine
postcontent:
I purchased another vehicle and I don't want her to just sit. I'm ready to let her go for a great price. Or trade for a sports bike, a sweet set of rims with brand new tires 5x100 or a LEGAL firearm. Talk to me but through email. 

ABOUT THE CAR: It's an 03 Hyundai Tiburon GT V6 6-Speed MANUAL transmission, clutch was replaced just a hair over a year ago so it's still gripping NICELY as I do not abuse this car because the last thing I need is a ticket. 159,xxx miles and counting. I am not the first owner, I believe I am the 3rd owner if I remember correctly from checking her Carfax over a year ago. The car has never been involved in an accident, broken into or vandalized. I recently(less than 3 months ago) installed brand new front axles and inner-outter tie-rods. Aways do oil changes on time and did a transmission fluid swap about a year ago. Those don't have to be done I believe every 75k miles or so I believe. All of the work on the car has been done by me except for the clutch. 

INTERIOR: Black leather interior that does show typical wear and tear, power windows and sunroof. I installed a short-throw shifter which helps you shift a bit quicker than the stock one. I also installed interior LED lights where your feet rest and also LED dome lights with a cool little LED ambient light similar to what some of the newer cars have now-a-days. The car came with an aftermarket head unit but it can't be operated because the face was broken off by a very curious nephew and cables already ran for an amplifier and subwoofer. I never installed a new radio because it's not something I cared for enough but I can hook you up with a new radio if you buy the car. Alpine speakers in the front and stocks in the rear. The yakima roof rack is off the car and it's staying with me. 

EXTERIOR: The factory color is a very dark blue, I plasti-dipped the entire car Olive Green(Military green) and added a bunch of graphics to make it look Militarized but I'm willing to remove the plasti dip only if you're serious. The entire rear(bumper, tail lights and muffler) of the car was swapped with the rear of an 07 Tiburon which looks way better than the 03. I installed a set of ZG Flares and the rims are 18x10 XRR 521s. I custom made the headlights from an extra set i had(not illegal). It has tint all around front: 35% all rear: 5%. No this car is not a cop magnet, I haven't been pulled over for anything other than my driving and even then I haven't gotten a single ticket on anything about my car. I have a Viper alarm/keyless/remote start system installed but I deactivated the remote start because it's dangerous to have on a manual transmission vehicle but everything else works great.

THE CONS: When my father took my car in for the clutch, the people who did it and put it back together didn't set the alignment perfectly so it does pull to the right a tad bit which to me doesn't really matter but we tried to go back to get it re aligned and they had closed literally 2 weeks after my clutch install. There's a small rust spot where cars this age typically get where the rear bumper meets the quarter panel on the driver side. Its maybe the size of a typical light bulb(only common thing i could think of). Last thing is since I drive to DC a lot, I park in garages all the time for work. While I was at work from what my friend believes it was, a truck with big tires backed into my passenger side fencer and ruined it which is why in the pictures above, it's red. Later that same week, I believe the same douchebag did it again but this time he missed my fender but damaged my rims lip, it's nothing big and structural but its there. An honorable mention would be my E brake doesn't like to be used in the winter because the brake line freezes which keeps the brakes engaged, I never use my e brake anyway because I leave it on gear but I believe it's something you should know. Other than these small problems the car is very very solid and runs as strong as when I first bought her.

Alright, I know thats a lot to read but I want to be as honest and as open as I can with this because buying a car isn't a small purchase. So now you know pretty much everything about my baby.

I appreciate taking your time to read all of this, let me know what you think!
